title: F12M1, liver, RNA-Seq
characteristics_ch1.1: generation and f0-treatment: F1 generation (From F0 Mixture exposed)
treatment_protocol_ch1: F0 generation exposure from the tadpole to the mature adult stage at a concentration (50 ng.L-1). Females from F1 and F2 generation were not exposed.
extract_protocol_ch1: For each biological replicate, the RNAqueous®-4PCR Kit (Ambion, Austin USA) was used to extract the total RNA from 15 mg of liver according to manufacturer instructions
extract_protocol_ch1.1: RNA-seq libraries were prepared using the TruSeq Stranded mRNA sample Prep kit (Illumina, San Diego, USA) and sequenced on an Illumina GAIIx sequencer as 75 bp reads
data_processing: Reads were filtered based on their length, pairing, and quality using Trimmomatic (v0.32.1)
data_processing.1: Cleaned reads were mapped to the Xenopus genome (10.0 assembly) using HISAT2.
data_processing.2: The Cufflinks (v0.0.7) tool was applied to HISAT2 alignments to enumerate the number of short reads overlapping the Ensembl annotated genes, for each library
data_processing.3: The Cuffmerge (v0.0.6) toll was used to merge transcriptome
data_processing.4: Cuffdiff (v0.0.7) toll was used for differential  gene expression  analysis. Control mRNAseq data have been have been deposited on NCBI Gene Expression Omnibus (GEO) (accession no GSE150911).
